<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Amal-Hizballah Tension Prevails in South </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Amal-Hizballah Tension Prevails in South </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0405080894 Kafr Killa Voice of the South in Arabic 0700 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0405080894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kafr Killa Voice of the South </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Our correspondent reports that tension is prevailing 
between the Amal Movement and Hizballah activists in 'Aytit and 
neighboring villages against a background of incidents involving 
the two parties in the past two days. The correspondent adds 
that the incidents took place after Hizballah elements provoked 
Amal Movement elements in the village. 
  Tension also prevails in Qa'qa'iyat al-Jisr and other 
villages in the al-Nabatiyah district after Amal Movement 
elements accused Hizballah elements of killing Amal official 
Ni'mah Haydar about two weeks ago. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

