<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mubarak Receives South Korean Envoy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mubarak Receives South Korean Envoy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0305183594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1755 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0305183594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 May (MENA) -- This evening in the 
Presidential Office, President Husni Mubarak received Dr. Han 
Wan-sang, personal envoy [name and title as received] of South 
Korean President Kim Yong-sam, who is visiting Egypt. 
  The Korean envoy said he delivered a message to President 
Mubarak from the South Korean president. He praised the 
relations linking Egypt and South Korea, noting that it is high 
time to develop these relations to the full to face up to the 
challenges following the Cold War era. 
  Touching on developments in Korea, the envoy said that ties 
of cooperation between the two Koreas could be developed if 
North Korea abandons its nuclear activity. In that case, our 
country could extend assistance to North Korea to help it become 
a full-fledged member of the international community and we 
could work together to achieve regional stability, he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

