<H3> <TI>   Oppositionists React to Signing of Self-Rule Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oppositionists React to Signing of Self-Rule Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    PFLP, DFLP Declare Day of Mourning </H4>

<F P=102> JN0305180794 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 3 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0305180794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The Popular Front for the 
Liberation of Palestine [PFLP] and the Democratic Front for the 
Liberation of Palestine [DFLP] have declared tomorrow, 
Wednesday, a day of national mourning and have asked the people 
of the occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip to observe a general 
strike. 
  In a statement distributed in the occupied territories 
today, 
the two fronts said that the implementation of the Gaza-Jericho 
agreement will constitute one of the most dangerous and 
difficult periods in the Palestinian people's struggle because 
complete coordination now exists between the Palestinian side 
and the occupation forces, as the statement put it. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

