<H4>    'Usfur on Israel Raising New Obstacles </H4>

<F P=102> NC0305140194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1340 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0305140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 May (MENA)--Hasan 'Usfur, member of the 
Palestinian delegation to the Palestinian-Israeli Security 
Affairs Committee, has disclosed that the new obstacles that 
Israel suddenly raised to the agreement on self-rule in Gaza and 
Jericho result from its putting forth 25 new points on all 
issues--security, civilian, and legal. 
  He told a MENA correspondent today that these points had 
been 
agreed upon earlier. 
  He said: This is a known Israeli tactic aimed at preventing 
us from making any new proposals. 

</TEXT>

