<H4>    Rabin-'Arafat Meeting Cut Off </H4>

<F P=102> TA0305202094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 2000 GMT 3 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0305202094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher is 
currently meeting with PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat. This meeting 
cut off the meeting between Prime Minister Rabin and 'Arafat. 
The forum of the Rabin-'Arafat meeting was expanded to include 
Ministers Peres and Sarid and Major General Amnon Shahaq, head 
of the Israeli peace delegation, on the Israeli side, and Nabil 
Sha'th, head of the Palestinian delegation, on the PLO side. 
Uri Savir, director general of the Foreign Ministry, and Yo'el 
Singer, the Foreign Ministry's legal adviser, later joined the 
talks as well. 
  While the meeting between Christopher and 'Arafat is going 
on, the meeting Ministers Peres, Sarid, and the Israeli 
delegation members are holding with the Palestinian 
representatives, headed by Nabil Sha'th, is continuing. Our 
correspondent Arye Gus notes that the inclusion of Savir and 
Singer indicates that the sides have reached the formulation 
stage. 

</TEXT>

