<H3> <TI>   Arms Control, Regional Security Meeting Opens </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arms Control, Regional Security Meeting Opens </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Israel Invites Arabs To Tour IDF Bases </H4>

<F P=102> TA0305191394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1800 GMT 3 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0305191394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Israeli delegation to the Qatar arms control 
talks has invited the neighboring countries participating in the 
multilateral talks to send delegations to visit IDF [Israel 
Defense Forces] bases and installations. Sources in the Israeli 
delegation said that even if the invitation is declined, this 
will not mean failure because the very fact that it was issued 
constitutes a small step forward that is indicative of a change 
in atmosphere. 
  Our correspondent in Qatar Karmela Menashe reports that the 
Israeli delegation is meeting with delegations from Arab states 
concurrently with the plenum sessions. Sources in the Israeli 
delegation said that progress has been made in the discussions 
of the committee on arms control. 
  The atmosphere in the meetings outside the plenum hall is 
relaxed. In all the sessions, all the participants are 
addressing the issue of Israel's nonconventional weapons arsenal. 
  The Qatari foreign minister will leave for Cairo tomorrow to 
attend the signing ceremony of the agreement between the PLO and 
Israel. 

</TEXT>

