<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Intermittent Sniper Fire Reported in Karachi; 2 Killed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Intermittent Sniper Fire Reported in Karachi; 2 Killed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0305160094 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0305160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Reports of intermittent sniper firing have been 
received from Liaqatabad, Khwaja Ajmer Nagri, New Karachi and 
Gulbahar areas of Karachi Central district. Nine people 
suffered gunshot injuries. Public transport has been affected, 
and shops are closed in the Karachi central district. Earlier, 
two persons succumbed to their injuries. Authorities have 
imposed Section 144 in the Karachi East district and banned the 
assembly of more than five people and the carrying of passengers 
on motorcycles. Reports of gunfire have also been reported from 
(?several) areas of Hyderabad. Contingents of police and law 
enforcement authorities are patrolling the affected areas. The 
district magistrate of Hyderabad in a press note has said that 
one person was killed and one injured in an incident involving 
gunfire in village No. 7 of Hyderabad [words indistinct]. A case 
has been filed, and investigations have begun. Two suspects 
have been arrested. 

</TEXT>

