<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Hariri Returns From Paris, Damascus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Hariri Returns From Paris, Damascus </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0305194694 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1900 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0305194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri returned to Beirut 
via Damascus this evening after a private visit to Paris. 
Al-Hariri left the French capital for Damascus this morning 
where he met with Syrian Vice President 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam 
and had lunch with him. He also met with a number of senior 
Syrian officials. As soon as he arrived in Beirut, al-Hariri 
contacted President Ilyas al-Hirawi and Chamber of Deputies 
Speaker Nabih Birri to discuss current developments with them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

