<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegation To Attend PLO-Israel Accord Signing Ceremony </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation To Attend PLO-Israel Accord Signing Ceremony </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0305111994 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 0900 GMT 3 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0305111994 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During a session led by Prime Minister Dr. 
'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali this morning, the cabinet decided to 
form a delegation, led by Talal Sat'an al-Hasan, minister of 
state for foreign affairs, along with Nayif Sa'ud al-Qadi, the 
Jordanian ambassador to Egypt, to represent Jordan at the 
signing of the Palestinian-Israeli agreement ceremony which will 
take place in Cairo tomorrow, Wednesday. 
  During its session, the cabinet reviewed the minutes of 
meetings of the committee in charge of preparing for the 
meetings of the Joint Jordanian-Egyptian Higher Committee. The 
higher committee began meetings at the Ministry of Planning 
yesterday to discuss fields of cooperation between the two 
fraternal countries in preparation for discussing and approving 
these minutes during its meetings on Thursday under Prime 
Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali and Egyptian Prime Minister 
Dr. 'Atif Sidqi. 

</TEXT>

