<H3> <TI>   Pakistani Interior Minister Arrives in Tehran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pakistani Interior Minister Arrives in Tehran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405100394 Tehran IRNA in English 0933 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405100394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 4, IRNA -- Pakistan regards the 
assassination of former Iranian cultural attache to Pakistan, 
Sadeq Ghanji, a great crime and is trying to arrest the murderer 
as soon as possible, said the visiting Pakistani minister of 
interior, Nasrullah Khan Babar. 
  Babar was referring to the recent escape of Ghanji's 
murderer 
from police custody in Pakistan. 
  Talking to the reporters upon arrival here Wednesday, Babar 
said that his delegation would discuss with Iranian officials 
issues of mutual interest including campaign against drug 
trafficking along Iran-Pakistan joint borders. 
  Iran's minister of interior, 'Ali Mohammed Besharati, who 
greeted his Pakistani counterpart at the airport, said that the 
two countries would explore avenues to intensify campaign 
against drug trafficking. 
  He further said that Iran was in the frontline of anti-drug 
campaign, adding that further cooperation between Iran and 
Pakistan would be fruitful in this regard. 

</TEXT>

