<H3> <TI>   Foreign Exchange Body Seeks To Stabilize Rial </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Exchange Body Seeks To Stabilize Rial </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405101794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405101794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning the Foreign Exchange Market Committee 
held a session chaired by President Hashemi-Rafsanjani. 
According to a Central News Unit report at the session a report 
was submitted to the president on the latest developments on 
Iran's outstanding debts and the successes achieved. 
  Owing to the country's foreign currency reserves situation 
it 
was decided that, to fight the corruption perpetrated by foreign 
currency dealers and to stabilize the exchange rate, in addition 
to providing foreign currency for [the import of] goods which 
qualify for official bank rates, the banking system will 
provide, at 50 rials below open market rates, all the foreign 
currency required by importers who have registered, or will 
register, at the Commerce Ministry to import in return for 
export. The banking system will also purchase the foreign 
currencies earned from exports, if the exporters are willing, at 
the same rate. A Central Bank statement will be issued on this 
soon. 

</TEXT>

