<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   IRNA Releases Trade Statistics </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IRNA Releases Trade Statistics </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305215894 Tehran IRNA in English 2118 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0305215894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 3, IRNA -- Some 17.61 million tons of 
non-oil commodities were imported into Iran over the past 12 
months. 
  91 percent were exported [as received] through ports, while 
the rest were exported through land routes. 
  The goods included 10.5 million tons of non-basic and 7.1 
million tons of basic goods. 98 percent of the goods were 
imported through land, and the remaining two percent through 
land routes. 
  According to public relations department of Roads and 
Transportation Ministry a total of 15.2 million tons of goods 
were loaded within the period which included 6.4 million tons of 
basic and 8.8 million tons of non-basic commodities. 

</TEXT>

