<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council Issues Warning on Energy Consumption </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council Issues Warning on Energy Consumption </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205120794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205120794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The country's Scientific Research Council warned 
today that the irregular increase in the consumption of oil 
products and energy waste will threaten our country's oil 
exports and create more problems for the country's oil-related 
income over the next decade. 
  According to our correspondent's report, the Scientific 
Research Council's energy committee today issued a report 
entitled "Perspectives of Energy Research in the Islamic 
Republic of Iran" at a seminar in which lecturers, researchers, 
and the country's executive officials in the energy sector were 
present. The report says: It is estimated that our country 
consumes more than one million barrels of oil each day. Even 
with the present low oil prices, the country is consuming around 
$5 billion worth of oil each year. That makes the need to 
rationalize our country's energy consumption, to develop 
consumption patterns, and to expand research into energy saving 
unavoidable . 
  The secretary of the state Scientific Research Council's 
energy committee also said: If the country's present trend of 
energy consumption continues, we will need to build a new 
refinery each year and that would cost a yearly investment of 
more than $1.5 billion. He added: Savings of 5.5 percent in 
energy consumption is realistic and can reduce foreign currency 
expenditure equivalent to $1.5 billion for investment in 
refining oil. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

