<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armenian Vice President `Regrets' Downing of Plane </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armenian Vice President `Regrets' Downing of Plane </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Arrives for 2-Day Talks </H4>

<F P=102> LD0305115694 Tehran IRNA in English 1113 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0305115694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 3, IRNA -- Armenian Vice-President Gagik 
Arutyunyan arrived here Tuesday on a two-day visit to hold talks 
with Iranian officials on the crash of an Iranian plane in 
Karabakh in March and to convey a message of condolence from the 
Armenian president to Iranian authorities. The Armenian 
official was greeted at Tehran's Mehrabad International Airport 
by Iranian Vice President for Economic Affairs Mohsen Nurbakhsh. 
  Speaking to IRNA upon arrival, Arutyunyan expressed regret 
over the incident, saying expert teams from Iran and the 
Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) were still 
investigating the issue to find out the cause of the crash. The 
Iranian passanger plane was downed near Stepanakert region in 
Karabakh on March 17, killing all its 32 passengers and crew on 
board. The victims were families of Iranian diplomats in Russia 
and Iranian students abroad. 
  Arutyunyan said that there were many ambigious points 
surrounding the crash which would be unraveled after the experts 
completed their invstigations. He said the staff of Armenia's 
control tower had done their best to prevent the plane from 
flying off its route. He promised "if the staff of the Armenian 
control tower are found guilty of negligence they will be 
punished." Arutyunyan added that during his stay here, he would 
discuss Iran-Armenia relations, expansion of bilateral ties and 
regional issues with President Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani, the 
Majlis vice speaker, the foreign minister, minister economic and 
financial affairs and his counterpart Nurbakhsh. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

