<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian Police To Enter Gaza, Jericho 8 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian Police To Enter Gaza, Jericho 8 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0505095594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0820 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0505095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 5 May (MENA)--Palestinian negotiator Hasan 
'Usfur has said that 1,000 Palestinian police will enter Gaza 
and Jericho on Sunday [8 May]. 
  The force will begin to take over the camps from which the 
Israeli Army will withdraw, he said. 
  'Usfur told MENA today that 22 Palestinian officers 
representing the Palestinian side in the Palestinian-Israeli 
Coordination and Cooperation Committee arrived in Gaza on 
Tuesday to prepare for the entry of the Palestinian police force. 
  He said 6,000 members of the force will enter the self-rule 
areas in the next two weeks. 
  It was agreed, he explained, that the Palestinian police 
force would consist of 9,000 personnel, 7,000 of which will come 
from outside the occupied territories and 2,000 from inside the 
self-rule areas. 
  'Usfur said that Israel yesterday released 850 Palestinian 
prisoners. He said the rest of the 5,000 prisoners whose 
release was agreed upon will be freed in batches over the next 
five weeks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

