<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Algeria: National Security and </F>
Foreign Intelligence Chiefs Replaced in Military Reshuffle"] 
  [Except] Algiers, AL-HAYAH -- Three days before the march 
to be staged in support of the dialogue in Algeria, President 
Major General Liamine Zeroual yesterday made changes among 
commanders of the military zones and some senior Army posts. 
  No information has leaked about the new appointments and 
changes among commanders of the military zones. The names of 
the commanders who have been pensioned off are surrounded by 
complete secrecy. However, a high-level source has revealed to 
AL-HAYAH that Fadil Saidi, director of foreign intelligence, has 
been moved to another post and that Gen. Tawfik, chief of the 
intelligence organs, is still in his post. 
  The ALGERIAN NEWS AGENCY announced in the afternoon that 
Mohamed Douadah had been appointed director of national 
security, replacing Mohamed Tolba, who has been in charge of 
national security since January 1992. [passage omitted] 

