<DATE1>  4 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two Explosions Reported in Baghdad 1 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two Explosions Reported in Baghdad 1 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0405172394 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0405172394 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to Iraqi opposition sources, two big 
explosions rocked Baghdad last on 1 May. These sources said 
that the first explosion was caused by a car-bomb near the 
Olympics Committee building on Filastin Street. After a short 
while, another explosion occurred in a nearby street. These 
sources noted that after the blasts, the regime's security 
agencies cordoned off the area and began an extensive search. 

</TEXT>

