<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Radio Reports Attacks on Iraqi Targets </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Radio Reports Attacks on Iraqi Targets </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0505072794 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0505072794 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Kurdistan Bureau of the Supreme Assembly of the 
Islamic Revolution in Iraq stated that on 28 April the Iraqi 
opposition forces pounded the governorate building, the 
intelligence directorate headquarters, and the Ba'th Party 
building in al-Nasiriyah Governorate with mortars, killing or 
injuring dozens of Iraqi henchmen. 
  A statement released by the bureau said that the 
revolutionaries launched an assault on 27 April at an inspection 
checkpoint belonging to the al-Qurnah security directorate, 
killing or injuring 25 agents and destroying two armored 
vehicles. On the same day, the revolutionaries attacked a large 
force composed of 45 armored vehicles and a large number of 
infantry men, who were preparing to launch an offensive on [name 
indistinct] in al-Nasiriyah marshland. They inflicted casualties 
on the force and prevented it from launching the assault. 
  The statement said that the Iraqi regime formed two military 
divisions under Qusayy, the dictator's son, and Muhammad, son of 
Barzan al-Tikriti. The two divisions' task is to quell any 
possible popular uprising. 
  On the Iraqi intelligence acts of terrorism in neighboring 
countries, the statement said that the regime's intelligence 
began some time ago to train a group of agents to send them to 
Iran to carry out acts of terror there. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

