<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talabani Denies Asking European Leaders To Arm Kurds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talabani Denies Asking European Leaders To Arm Kurds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0405134094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 1 May 94 p5 </F>
<F P=103> PM0405134094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Talabani: I Did Not Request Arms From </F>
the Europeans"] 
  [Text] London, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Iraqi Kurdish Leader 
Jalal Talabani told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT yesterday that he did not 
ask the officials in Paris and the other European countries he 
recently visited to supply the Iraqi Kurds with arms. 
  He said that his talks with these officials covered a 
request 
for assistance in training local Kurdish police forces for 
maintaining internal security and protecting employees of the 
United Nations and the relief organizations operating in Iraqi 
Kurdistan. 
  He added that French Defense Minister Leotard, British 
Minister of State at the Foreign Office Douglas Hogg, and 
Spanish Foreign Minister Javier Solana "expressed willingness to 
study that request and inform us of their position later on, and 
so did the German officials I met with previously." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

