<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister: Plans for Jericho Bypass Road Ready </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister: Plans for Jericho Bypass Road Ready </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0405120994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 4 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0405120994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Construction and Housing Minister Binyamin 
Ben-Eli'ezer informed the Knesset today that the planning of the 
Jericho bypass road has been completed. Our correspondent Hayim 
Hecht reports that replying to a query from Knesset Member Limor 
Livnat, Minister Ben-Eli'ezer announced that the Civil 
Administration has started expropriating lands along the planned 
road. The tenders will be announced in three days and the works 
will start within two weeks. The construction and housing 
minister promised that the road will be completed within three 
months. 

</TEXT>

