<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soldiers Injured, Settlers Arrested in Incidents </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Soldiers Injured, Settlers Arrested in Incidents </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0505044894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 5 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0505044894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two soldiers were injured in stone-throwing 
incidents in the territories yesterday. Near Nabulus, a soldier 
suffered medium injuries when a military vehicle in which he was 
traveling came under a hail of stones. He was taken to 
Beilinson Hospital for treatment. The village of Hawwarah, 
where the incident took place, is under curfew. 
  In Jericho, a soldier suffered light injuries when local 
residents threw stones and bottles at the police station at the 
center of town. 
  During the night, dozens of right-wing activists and 
settlers 
continued their efforts to try to reach the ancient Jewish 
synagogue in Jericho. Part of the town has been declared a 
closed military area. A Qol Yisra'el reporter says soldiers 
were busy chasing those trying to infiltrate. Several arrests 
were made. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

