<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jordanian-Egyptian Committee Meetings Begin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jordanian-Egyptian Committee Meetings Begin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0305172294 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1500 GMT 3 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0305172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A meeting of the Jordanian-Egyptian Political 
Coordination Committee was held at the Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs today as part of the meetings of the Experts Committee, 
which is holding its preparatory meetings in Amman. 
  The Jordanian side was led by Nayif al-Hadid, secretary 
general of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, whereas the Egyptian 
side was led by Ambassador Badr Hammam, assistant foreign 
minister for Arab affairs. The two sides stressed the 
importance of enhancing bilateral relations in all fields and on 
various Arab, regional, and international issues as well as 
exchanging views on them. 
  The two sides also reviewed the new Arab and international 
changes and their impact on the Arab region on various 
political, economic, and other levels. 
  Talal al-Hasan, minister of state for foreign affairs, 
received and welcomed the Egyptian delegation. He stressed the 
deep bilateral ties that contribute to serving the supreme Arab 
interest. 

</TEXT>

