<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Egypt's Sadqi Arrives for Meetings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Egypt's Sadqi Arrives for Meetings </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0405200194 Amman Jordan Television Network in English 1900 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0405200194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News at Ten" program] </F>
  [Text] Egyptian Prime Minister 'Atif Sadqi flew to Amman 
this evening to attend meetings of the Joint Jordanian-Egyptian 
Committee on cooperation. He was greeted by Prime Minister Dr. 
'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali. 
  The Egyptian prime minister said he hoped the committee 
meetings would strengthen cooperation between the two countries. 
  [Begin Sidqi recording] We hope by renewing the meetings, 
this joint committee, the Jordanian-Egyptian Higher Committee, 
would strengthen the relations between our two countries for the 
benefit not only for Egypt or Jordan but for all the Arab 
people. [end recording] 
  "News at Ten" asked Prime Minister al-Majali about his 
impressions following today's signing of the PLO-Israeli 
agreement in Cairo. 
  [Begin al-Majali recording] I am a very optimistic man, all 
my life, so I am not going to change this time, and I think I am 
still optimistic and I always look forward to the 
implementation. And what I felt today, there is a real spirit 
of having honest implementation. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

