<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Buwayz Reacts to `Shamefaced' Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Buwayz Reacts to `Shamefaced' Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0405145194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1400 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0405145194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Commenting on the limited self-rule agreement that 
was signed between the Palestinians and Israelis in Cairo today, 
Foreign Minister Faris Buwayz said: We do not believe this 
agreement fulfills all the ambitions we had for the Palestinian 
people. This agreement does not spell out clearly the future of 
these negotiations nor is it committed to recognizing a 
Palestinian state, political rights, or the human rights of the 
refugees. He added: proceeding from this premise, we are not 
among those who are enthusiastic about or applaud this 
agreement. But since the PLO broke away from Arab solidarity 
and coordination, which was in its own interests, and since all 
we wanted from this coordination was to stress our moral 
obligation to the Palestinian cause, all we can do is to wish 
the PLO success, despite this agreement's being shamefaced 
[khajulan] in terms of its results. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

