<H3> <TI>   Bishops Criticize Church Bombing Investigation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bishops Criticize Church Bombing Investigation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0405135494 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1300 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0405135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At their monthly meeting today, the Maronite bishops 
stated that the continuing detentions and investigations since 
the bombing of the Sayyidat al-Najat Church have done nothing to 
reassure the public. They said that the focus is shifting from 
the Sayyidat al-Najat Church file to other files, that this 
crime has been removed from official attention, and that it has 
been used as a means for political rather than criminal trial. 
  The Maronite bishops denounced what they called the pursuit 
of many youths, which may harm Lebanon's reputation. They 
stressed that media freedom is the basis of freedoms. They 
noted that the issuing of the prospective media law will be a 
healthy sign if it guarantees freedom of expression. They 
called on officials to show serious attention to the people's 
economic difficulties. 

</TEXT>

