<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Welcomes PLO-Israeli Accord on Self-Rule </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Welcomes PLO-Israeli Accord on Self-Rule </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0505055494 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0505055494 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] India and several other countries have welcomed the 
signing of the historic agreement on Palestinian self-rule. An 
External Affairs Ministry spokesman said in New Delhi that India 
has given consistent support to the Palestinians in the peace 
process. He recalled that India is one of the few countries 
outside the region invited to witness the signing ceremony at 
Cairo. The Indian delegation led by the minister of state for 
external affairs, Mr. R.L. Bhatia, was present when the PLO 
chairman, Mr Yasir 'Arafat and the Israeli prime minister, Mr. 
Rabin, signed the landmark agreement. 

</TEXT>

