<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Central Bank Governor on Foreign Currency Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central Bank Governor on Foreign Currency Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405194594 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1630 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Studio interview with Dr. Mohammad Hoseyn 'Adeli, governor </F>
of the Central Bank of Iran, by unidentified correspondent; date 
not given -- live or recorded] 
  [Excerpts] [passage omitted] ['Adeli] [passage omitted] 
The setting up of non-banking establishments will truly change 
the state monetary system. The government approved the policy 
today. I should explain that according to that policy from now 
on our private sector will also be able to set up non-banking 
credit establishments. 
  As you know, at the moment in our country only banks deal 
with money matters. [passage omitted] In a developing country, 
which needs more investments; more savings, there is a need for 
more instruments to attract people's savings. That is why in 
many developing and developed countries non-banking 
establishments exist. We also decided to create such non-banking 
establishments in order to offer, on the one hand, a more 
diverse variety for people's investments and, on the other hand, 
to be able to offer loans. The only difference between those 
institutions and banks is that they cannot issue written credit 
documents. That is they cannot offer check books to the public. 
They can offer all types of saving accounts and offer all type 
of loans, but they cannot offer any current accounts. In our 
announcement next week we shall set out all their conditions so 
that those seeking to set up such establishments can apply 
accordingly. God willing, such establishments will begin 
operation in our country and a better efficiency is brought 
about in the country in the allocation of resources. 
  [Correspondent] Thank you, Dr. 'Adeli, for your 
explanations. 

</TEXT>

