<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trading in Foreign Currency Markets Called `Treason' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trading in Foreign Currency Markets Called `Treason' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405184894 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1630 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At a Cabinet session today, a recent decision by the 
committee for regulating the foreign currency market was raised, 
which relates to the supply of foreign currency to those 
importers who have registered or will be registering at the 
Ministry of Commerce for imports in lieu of their exports. It 
was decided that the banking system will follow the policy 
diligently and that the companies and establishments owned by 
the government or affiliated to it will avoid participation in 
the foreign currency market. 
  Taking into consideration the readiness of the banking 
system 
to supply the foreign currency requirements of this group of 
importers, the presence of state companies and those companies 
affiliated to the government in the foreign currency market will 
be deemed treason and offenders will be prosecuted. 
  According to a decision by the Cabinet, any negligence by 
executive banks in carrying out the new decisions by the foreign 
currency regulating committee will be deemed as collaboration 
with saboteurs of the state currency and economic system. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-58542 </DOCNO>
