<F P=102>   LD0405172494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405172494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Islamic Republic of Iran's Foreign Ministry 
issued a statement today expressing satisfaction at the 
dismantling of apartheid in South Africa and the victory of the 
African National Congress in that country's elections. The 
statement announced: Our country is ready to do all it can to 
expand bilateral relations in all fields. 
  The statement refers to the Islamic Republic of Iran's 
support for the struggle of the people of South Africa to 
eliminate racism and for cooperation with black struggling 
groups and adds: The Islamic Republic of Iran has always 
supported the establishment of a popular government in South 
Africa through a general election in which all races 
participate, and which is based on the principle of one person, 
one vote. It is in that respect that Iran has sent four 
diplomats, through the United Nations, as observers to the 
elections in South Africa. 

</TEXT>

