<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Berates Indian Charges of Kashmir Involvement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Berates Indian Charges of Kashmir Involvement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0405152194 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0405152194 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has said that India is vitiating the 
mutual atmosphere by harping upon the baseless and malicious 
allegations of Pakistan's involvement in Kashmir and some other 
parts of India. A Foreign Office spokesman commenting on the 
recent propaganda campaign against Pakistan launched by Indian 
Government said that Indian Government is trying to divert 
attention from its own failures and brutalities in held Kashmir. 
The Muslim ambassadors based in New Delhi after visiting the 
occupied Kashmir have observed that gross violation of human 
rights are taking place in the valley and the Kashmiris hate 
India. One of the members of the delegation -- the Iranian 
ambassador, Mr. ('Ali Raza Shaykh Ata) -- in a statement has 
said that the program presented to the delegation in New Delhi 
was never implemented. He said the members of the delegation 
were not allowed to visit Hazratbal shrine, Sopor and Bijbiara. 
He said the meeting with the leaders of Hurriet Conference was 
not arranged and we were not allowed even to meet and talk with 
the common people in the valley. 

</TEXT>

