<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To End Public Execution of Criminals </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To End Public Execution of Criminals </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0405160294 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0405160294 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government has decided as a matter of policy not 
to carry out executions of criminals sentenced to death in 
public despite the powers vested in it to do so under Section 10 
of the Special Courts for Speedy Trials Act 1992. The present 
government respects the human dignity and upholds the human 
values as upheld by the civilized and progressive societies of 
the world. 

</TEXT>

