<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   IDF Confirms `Only' 380 Prisoners Freed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IDF Confirms `Only' 380 Prisoners Freed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0405202094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 2000 GMT 4 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0405202094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] has only released 
approximately 380 Palestinian prisoners. Approximately 250 
freed prisoners arrived in the Gaza Strip and the remainder in 
Judaea and Samaria. This was reported by Palestinian sources 
this evening to our correspondent Moti Amir. 
  The sources claimed that the IDF had presented erroneous 
figures and misled the media with regard to the exact number 
prisoners released. Our correspondent notes that IDF sources 
this evening confirmed that due to last-minute technical 
problems, less than 400 Palestinian prisoners were released 
today, and not 1,000 as originally intended. 

</TEXT>

