<H3> <TI>   Al-Zahhar Terms 4 May `Black Day' for Palestinians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Zahhar Terms 4 May `Black Day' for Palestinians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0405141694 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 4 May 94 pp 1, 18 </F>
<F P=103> TA0405141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By 'Ala' al-Mashahrawi] </F>
  [Excerpt] Gaza -- Dr. Mahmud al-Zahhar has described the 
day of the signing of the Palestinian-Israeli agreement as a 
black day for the Palestinian people and a day of mourning and 
grief to all those who love Jerusalem and Palestine and are 
aware of the nature of the conflict on this land. 
  In his statement to AL-QUDS, Dr. al-Zahhar stressed the 
Islamic Movement's rejection of the agreement that is expected 
to be signed today in Cairo between 'Arafat and Rabin. He said: 
History will not stop on this day or on any such event. Muslim 
history has proved that it has surmounted such days and that the 
journey of victory might be delayed but it is inevitable and 
certain. 
  Al-Zahhar added: Those signing the agreement will bear its 
results, consequences, and repercussions before God, the people, 
and history. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

