<H3> <TI>   PFLP Leader Habash Criticizes Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PFLP Leader Habash Criticizes Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0405191494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0405191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone interview with George Habash, secretary general </F>
of the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine, by 
correspondent Muhammad Bishkar "soon after the signing of the 
Palestinian-Israeli accord"; place not given -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Habash] It [the Palestinian-Israeli accord] fully 
undermines the sacrifices and struggle of the Palestinian people 
over more than 25 years. It undermines the right of the 
Palestinian people to self-determination and the resolutions of 
the national councils, even the UN resolutions that we do not 
believe achieve all the Palestinian people's demands. This 
accord has also given up on these resolutions. 
  Needless to say, the economic accord recently signed in 
Paris 
which places not only Palestine, but also the entire Arab region 
and the Middle East [sentence incomplete as heard] and opens the 
door to the Arab and Middle East region. This issue also 
concerns you, I mean Iran. Why? Because this accord opens the 
door to the entire Middle Eastern region. 

</TEXT>

