<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   DFLP Member: Agreement `Capitulation Agreement' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DFLP Member: Agreement `Capitulation Agreement' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0405170694 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0405170694 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Taysir Khalid, member of the Democratic Front for 
the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP] Political Bureau, has said 
that, by all standards, the agreement between Israel and the PLO 
is a capitulation agreement. In a statement today, Khalid said 
that the formula of the agreement and its supplements consecrate 
the isolation of Jerusalem from the occupied territories, 
suspend the Palestinian people's right to sovereignty over their 
territories, and give Israel the right to control crossing 
points, borders, and foreign security. 
  He said that the agreement was not presented to the PLO 
organizations, especially the Palestine National Council, which 
did not authorize the PLO Executive Committee to sign the 
agreement. He called on the Palestinian people to unite their 
ranks and continue resisting the occupation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

