<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PFLP, DFLP Reject Cairo Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PFLP, DFLP Reject Cairo Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0405180594 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0405180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine 
[PFLP] said that signing the Israel-PLO agreements in Cairo and 
in Paris confirms Israel's success in circumventing the 
implementation of resolutions of international legitimacy, 
including UN Security Council Resolutions 242 and 338. In a 
press statement today, the PFLP's official spokesman said that 
the signing of the agreements enables Israel to consecrate its 
occupation and illegal measures such as building settlements, 
confiscating territories, annexing and judaizing Jerusalem, and 
continuing economic hegemony over the occupied territories. 
  The PFLP spokesman said that the front is not obligated by 
the agreements reached and that it will continue to struggle 
until the Palestinian people's objectives are achieved. 
  The Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP] 
said that the Cairo agreement, which was signed today, brought 
to light all the misleading, cheating, and false claims on the 
nature of self rule in Gaza and Jericho. The DFLP explained 
that withdrawal has been replaced by redeployment, noting that 
the presence of settlements was legitimized by the fact that the 
Oslo team recognized these settlements and agreed to have their 
security protected by Palestinians. 
  In a statement distributed today, the DFLP said that the 
agreement opens the door to normalizing Arab-Israeli relations 
which threaten the fate of all Arab territories under occupation 
and the future of the Palestinian people. The statement adds: 
As the DFLP rejects the agreement and condemns those who signed 
it, it announces that the agreement is not binding to the 
Palestinian people and that it will continue its struggle to 
achieve the Palestinian people's right to liberate their 
territories from the occupation, to achieve self-determination, 
and to establish their independent state. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

