<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Addresses Rally of Supporters Upon Return </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin Addresses Rally of Supporters Upon Return </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0405192294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 4 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0405192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin called on all 
supporters of the government's policy not to pay heed to those 
who rejoiced over spilled blood. The bloodshed was not 
attributable to the peace process but rather the result of false 
messianic beliefs and the hostility of the other side. The 
prime minister was speaking at a mass rally in Tel Aviv a short 
while after his return from Cairo. 
  Rabin called on his supporters to show more spirit and tell 
the enemies of peace in Israel that they did not represent the 
public. The Israeli people want peace and we will achieve it, 
Yitzhaq Rabin asserted. 

</TEXT>

