<H3> <TI>   President, Others Depart for Damascus Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President, Others Depart for Damascus Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0505093194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0800 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0505093194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An expanded Lebanese-Syrian summit is scheduled to 
be held in Damascus this morning involving President Ilyas 
al-Hirawi, Chamber of Deputies Speaker Nabih Birri, Prime 
Minister Rafiq al-Hariri, and Foreign Minister Faris Buwayz on 
the Lebanese side and Syrian President Hafiz 'al-Asad on the 
Syrian side. 
  The Lebanese president, speaker, prime minister, and foreign 
minister left for Damascus at 1000 today. 
  Before leaving Beirut, President al-Hirawi met U.S. 
Ambassador Mark Hambley and discussed local and regional 
developments. 

</TEXT>

