<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paper Condemns 'Arafat's `Complete Surrender' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paper Condemns 'Arafat's `Complete Surrender' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505095594 Tehran IRNA in English 0935 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0505095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 5, IRNA-- A Persian daily here Thursday 
blasted the Wednesday's signing of final documents on 
Gaza-Jericho compromise deal between Yasir 'Arafat and the 
Zionist regime and termed it as complete surrender to the 
Zionist enemy. The morning Persian daily `JOMHURI-YE ESLAMI' 
said in its editorial that the entire occupied territories 
plunged into strike and protest against the treacherous measure. 
The agreement is so scandalous that even 'Arafat primarily 
refused to sign its map appendix but eventually he was forced to 
do so under the U.S. pressures, the daily said. 
  Although the Zionist enemy and its supporters intend to 
suppress and uproot the Palestine Islamic movement through their 
bullying methods, they should realize that 'Arafat is not the 
representative of the Palestinian nation. 
  Lashing out at some of the reactionary Arab regimes for 
their 
collective treachery, it said that such regimes are not the 
guardians of the Palestinian nation. The daily added that the 
Palestinians have shown through their active presence in the 
occupied territories that they will not give in to such bullying 
acts. The paper stressed that the intifadah, the all-out 
uprising of the Palestinian nation, will have the final word in 
the occupied territories, adding that, the final word is the 
elimination of the occupying regime of Qods [Jerusalem]. 
  Liberation of the occupied territories and annihilation of 
the usurpers is the only option before the Palestinian nation, 
concluded the paper. 

</TEXT>

