<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bhutto To Attend South Africa Presidential Ceremony </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bhutto To Attend South Africa Presidential Ceremony </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0405131794 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 
1100 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0405131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It has been announced in Islamabad that the prime 
minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, will leave for South Africa on 
Sunday to attend the ceremony at which Mr. Nelson Mandela will 
be installed as the first non-White president of the country. 
The prime minister during her three-day official visit will 
hold bilateral meetings with several heads of state and 
government who will be present at this ceremony. On her way 
back, the prime minister will make a brief stopover in Nairobi. 

</TEXT>

