<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Update on Events 4, 5 May; Fighting Reported in Dhamar </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Source' Denies Warplane From South Downed </H4>

<F P=102> EA0405194194 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1500 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0405194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source at the Defense Ministry has 
denied a report on 3 May from the REUTER news agency citing a 
responsible military source that the northern Yemeni forces shot 
down a southern Yemeni Mig-21 fighter aircraft. The responsible 
source said the report was totally untrue. 
  The source also rejected the report of the television's 
first 
channel yesterday evening quoting a military spokesman of the 
Defense Ministry and the leadership of the General Staff of the 
movement of the 'Abbas, Taysir, and Milhim Brigades toward the 
former border areas in Shabwah. The source said this report was 
not only completely untrue but was aimed at obfuscating the 
continuing military reinforcements of the forces of the ruling 
family in Sanaa, being provocatively sent to the former border 
and toward the military units transferred from the southern to 
the northern governorates after unity, in accordance with the 
design to pounce on unity and democracy by attacking the active 
and generous forces standing in the way of the adventurist 
al-Ahmar family's plan to impose military rule. 

</TEXT>

