<H3> <TI>   Update on Events 4, 5 May; Fighting Reported in Dhamar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Update on Events 4, 5 May; Fighting Reported in Dhamar </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Salih Declares State of Emergency </H4>

<F P=102> JN0505064794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0625 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0505064794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unscheduled announcement of "State of Emergency" decree, </F>
issued by the Presidency in Sanaa on 5 May] 
  [Text] Republican decree No. 20 of 1994 declaring a state 
of emergency: 
  The chairman of the Presidential Council, taking cognizance 
of the Constitution of the Republic of Yemen and the law on the 
state of emergency and Law No. 1962 of 1991 on the establishment 
of the National Defense Council; in view of the eruption of 
internal sedition in the country due to the rebellion of 
secessionist elements in the leadership of the Yemeni Socialist 
Party against the Constitutional legitimacy, and subsequent 
military actions and the direct threat to the unity of the 
homeland and the security and stability of the citizens; 
according to the Council of Minister's presentation and in 
accordance with the assessment of the National Defense Council 
on the need to declare a state of emergency; in accordance with 
the requirements of the supreme national interest; and following 
the approval of the Presidential Council, decides: 
  Article 1: A state of emergency shall be declared as of 0800 
today, Thursday, 25 Dhi al-Qi'dah, 1414 Hegira, corresponding to 
5 May 1994, in all parts of the Republic for 30 days. 
  Article 2: Based on Article 97 of the Constitution of the 
Republic of Yemen, this decree shall be presented to the House 
of Representatives within a period of time not exceeding seven 
days as of its date. 
  Article 3: This decree shall be enforced as of the time and 
date of its issuance. It shall be published in the official 
gazette. 
  Issued at the Republic's presidency in Sanaa on 25 Dhi 
al-Qi'dah, 1414 Hegira, corresponding to 5 May 1994. 
  [Signed] Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman 
of 
the Presidential Council; 
  Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar, deputy prime minister 

</TEXT>

