<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Update on Events 4, 5 May; Fighting Reported in Dhamar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Update on Events 4, 5 May; Fighting Reported in Dhamar </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    President Orders Fighting Stopped </H4>

<F P=102> NC0505073094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2225 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0505073094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 4 May (MENA) -- A military source at the 
Ministry of Defense in Sanaa has stated that President 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih has issued orders to the Defense Ministry and 
the General Staff to stop the fighting that broke out earlier in 
Dhamar, south of Sanaa. He also asked the commander of the 
Republican Guard Battalion, northern, to halt the fighting 
unilaterally. 
  The source accused the Basahib Camp forces, southern, of 
starting the fighting this evening and charged that influential 
forces in the Yemeni Socialist Party are embarked on a plan to 
divide Yemen. 
  The source accused the same parties of attacking the Central 
Security personnel in Aden this evening and encircling and 
shelling their camps with tank artillery. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

