<H3> <TI>   Update on Events 4, 5 May; Fighting Reported in Dhamar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Update on Events 4, 5 May; Fighting Reported in Dhamar </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Plane Shot Down 5 May; Airport `Normal' </H4>

<F P=102> NC0505073894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0655 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0505073894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 5 May (MENA) -- An official Yemeni source has 
said that an aircraft for the southern forces tried to attack 
Sanaa airport this morning, but the air defense forces managed 
to shoot it down. 
  The source told a MENA correspondent in Sanaa that the 
situation at the airport is normal. 

</TEXT>

