<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Update on Events 4, 5 May; Fighting Reported in Dhamar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Update on Events 4, 5 May; Fighting Reported in Dhamar </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    House Withdraws Confidence in YSP </H4>

<F P=102> JN0505100894 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0935 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0505100894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unscheduled announcement] </F>
  [Text] Dear listeners, we have received the following: 
  The House of Representatives held a session this morning 
under its Speaker Shaykh 'Abdallah Bin-Husayn al-Ahmar to 
discuss the latest military developments in the country. The 
House called on all the masses of the Yemeni people to stand by 
Constitutional legitimacy and rally around the legitimate 
political leadership under brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Presidential Council and 
supreme commander of the Armed Forces. The House also called on 
all officers, noncommissioned officers, and personnel of the 
Armed and Security Forces in the Republic of Yemen to rally 
around the Supreme Command of the Armed Forces and not to obey 
orders unless they are issued by the supreme commander of the 
Armed Forces. 
  The House also decided to withdraw confidence in the 
secessionist elements in the leadership of the [Yemeni] 
Socialist Party [YSP] for their persistent wrongdoing which 
reached the extent of raiding the capital Sanaa and the two 
cities of Ta'izz and al-Hudaydah with aircraft and frightening 
the inhabitants and disturbing sleeping children. The House of 
Representatives also ratified the declaration of a state of 
emergency and authorized the political leadership to issue the 
necessary decisions to deal with the situation through which the 
country is passing. The people's deputies also decided to keep 
the House in open session. 
  The House has earlier reviewed and ratified the minutes of 
its previous session. 

</TEXT>

