<H4>    `Heavy' Gunfire Heard Around Palace </H4>

<F P=102> NC0505122194 Paris AFP in English 1214 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0505122194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dubai, May 5 (AFP) -- Heavy gunfire broke out around 
the presidential palace early Thursday and rival north and south 
forces bombed the country's two main airports in Sanaa and Aden. 
  Diplomatic sources contacted from the United Arab Emirates 
said a plan to evacuate Western nationals could be put into 
action in the next few hours amid the worsening crisis. 

</TEXT>

