<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Update on Events 4, 5 May; Fighting Reported in Dhamar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Update on Events 4, 5 May; Fighting Reported in Dhamar </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Official Source Welcomes U.S. Statement </H4>

<F P=102> JN0505122794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0505122794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An official source at the Yemeni Foreign Ministry 
has welcomed the statement the U.S. State Department issued 
yesterday evening on the current developments in our country. 
The source noted the statement's emphasis on the importance of 
convening the Constitutional institutions and the return of the 
official leadership to Sanaa in order to work as one team. He 
also noted the statement's call for disengaging the units and 
refraining from the use of force. 
  The official source expressed Yemen's appreciation of the 
American interest in preserving unity, democracy, security, and 
stability in our country and in the need to be guided by 
Constitutional legitimacy. The source said the American 
statement goes in the direction of what the legitimate and 
Constitutional leadership in the Republic of Yemen is proposing 
on the need to resolve the political crisis by peaceful means 
and within the framework of the pledge and accord document 
unanimously endorsed by the Yemeni people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

